In early winter, the semi-desert grassland by Qinghai Lake becomes a wasteland. Przewalski's gazelles begin to suffer food shortages. The streams are frozen, depriving them of water sources. Once every year, the Przewalski's gazelles set off for an extraordinary journey. It's not just about survival. They are called on a mission to reproduce. Check out video to see how the animals survive the migration! About 'Journeys in Nature': Snowy Qinghai Lake Series Qinghai Lake, the largest saltwater, inland lake in China, is home to a large number of wild animals. CGTN Nature's film crew traveled to Qinghai and discovered rare animal and plant species. During the Spring Festival, we will present the beautiful nature of China â€“ "Journeys in Nature": Snowy Qinghai Lake Series, showing the wonderful creatures in winter. For more: Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 1: Snowy Lake Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 2: Swan lake on ice (Cover image is a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)